    "This representation is obtained simply by transporting the representation of H g formed by M g using an isomorphismH g → H g ′ = hH g h -1,(125)induced byg ′ = hgh -1.",
    "(126)This recovers the d = 2, [ω g] = 0 piece of the statement 1.6.",
    "Three dimensions.In three spacetime dimensions, the twisted sector operators for a 0-form symmetry are line operators:L D (g) 2.",
    "(127)Line operators L in the g-twisted sector for a 0-form symmetry G (0) are part of a multiplet M comprised of line operators, which lie in twisted sectors for elements in the conjugacy class[g] ⊆ G (0).The stabilizer H g transforms a g-twisted sector line in M back into a g-twisted sector line in M, but the identity of the g-twisted sector line may get transformed as we already discussed for untwisted sector line operators.",
    "In total, repeating the arguments of section 2.2 we learn that the line operators in M lying in the g-twisted sector form a 2-representation ρ (2) g of H g, recovering the d = 3, [ω g] = 0 piece of the statement 1.6.The line operators in M lying in g ′ -twisted sector for g ′ = g ′′ g g ′′-1 form a 2-representation ρ(2)g ′ of the isomorphic group H g ′ = g ′′ H g g ′′-1,(128) where ρ (2)g ′ is obtained by transporting ρ (2) g using the isomorphism provided by the above equation."
